name: 5, -75 @ 1870 masl
description:
Lucero after carrying coffee seedlings uphill.
3/15 of the series.

Land is never really owned, just managed. Our lease is temporary, as nature does not answer to the time of humans.

We do not control it, we cannot turn the inherent chaos into order. Our job is to embrace it, manage it, and deliver the outputs. Thus, it requires love and enjoyement. The will to follow the process.

Part of 'This is El Bocadillo'.
Casabianca, Tolima, Colombia
2017
